<section id="how" style="background: linear-gradient(180deg, transparent, rgba(244,237,224,0.015), transparent);">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-label"><span class="idx">02 -</span> The ritual</div>
    <h2 class="heading">From <em>git push</em> to a page your grandmother can read.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">
      The whole pipeline, plain. No CI to configure, no yaml to bless. You focus on writing;
      Porvi handles the choreography.
    </p>

    <div class="flow">
      <div class="term">
        <div class="term-head">
          <div class="term-dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
          <div class="term-title">~/projects/almanac-site</div>
        </div>
        <div class="term-body">
          <span class="line"><span class="mute"># link a new site</span></span>
          <span class="line"><span class="prompt">$</span>porvi link <span class="mute">almanac.noctua.co</span></span>
          <span class="line mute">  · detected astro@4.8 · node 20</span>
          <span class="line mute">  · repo → gh:noctua/almanac</span>
          <span class="line good">  ✓ site linked</span>
          <span class="blank"></span>
          <span class="line"><span class="prompt">$</span>git push</span>
          <span class="line mute">  · build 3a9f - 11.8s</span>
          <span class="line mute">  · cache · 47 files warm</span>
          <span class="line good">  ✓ live &nbsp;<span class="mute">→</span> almanac.noctua.co</span>
          <span class="blank"></span>
          <span class="line mute"># preview a branch</span>
          <span class="line"><span class="prompt">$</span>porvi preview <span class="mute">feature/spring-issue</span></span>
          <span class="line good">  ✓ preview-spring-8f2.porvi.site</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <div class="n">01</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Bring the project</h4>
            <p>
              Any Astro repo works - public, private, fresh, or decades old. Porvi respects
              what you already have.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="n">02</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Claim the domain</h4>
            <p>
              Add a record. We handle the cert, the edge routing, and the invisible boring
              parts. You see "live" when it's live.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="n">03</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Keep writing</h4>
            <p>
              Every push is a deploy. Every branch is a preview. Every rollback is one
              command. That's it - that's the product.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
